description: From modern Latin Altrices (a former division of birds), plural of altrix, the feminine of altor ‘nourisher’, from alere ‘nourish’.

adjectives.description: altricial (comparative more altricial, superlative most altricial)

entries.meaning: (zoology) Helpless at birth (of young animals); or having young which are helpless at birth.
examples: First, humans are altricial, with immature newborns and a long childhood.
